    {
      "text": "Darxide (stylized as DarXide) is a shoot 'em up video game developed by Frontier Developments and published by Sega for the 32X.  It was one of the last releases for the console with only a European release in January 1996. Gameplay is similar to that of Asteroids in three dimensions. Players must destroy a number of space rocks in order to complete each level.\nReception of Darxide was mixed. The game was followed in 2004 by Darxide EMP, an expanded version released for Pocket PCs and Nokia mobile phones.",
